<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2556] log4j-1.2-api works only with core</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2556</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Logger implementation of log4j-1.2-api casts to org.apache.logging.log4j.core.LoggerContext. This works only if the provider of log4j(2) is the default (&quot;core&quot;) provider. I have written my own provider that includes its own implementation of a LoggerContext (properly implementing &quot;org.apache.logging.log4j.spi.LoggerContext&quot;, of course). So the cast fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMHO log4j-1.2-api should work with any implementation of a log4j(2) provider.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13218081">LOG4J2-2556</key>
